-- Bernanke Welcomes Students Competing in Economics Contest
-- B y   J o s h u a   Z u m b r u n
-- 2012-11-27T14:04:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-27/bernanke-welcomes-students-competing-in-economics-contest.html
Federal Reserve Chairman Ben S. Bernanke welcomed college students to an annual competition the
central bank hosts where teams from five different schools will
give presentations on monetary policy.  Bernanke did not discuss the outlook for monetary policy or
the economy in his remarks. Speaking in  Washington , Bernanke
said he will “be looking forward to the solutions that these
groups come up with.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joshua Zumbrun in Washington at 
 jzumbrun@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
